CML; 2) unplanned pregnancies with CML; 3) CML diagnosed during pregnancy.
EXPERT OPINION: Confidence in managing pregnancy and CML continues to grow. In 
the majority of cases, with careful planning and counseling, no treatment is 
required and disease control can be safely regained after pregnancy ends. For 
those who require treatment, various options are available and there is growing 
evidence to suggest that some TKIs may be safe in the later stages of pregnancy.

